# ── Local Supabase stack (the daily-driver dev backend) ──────────────────────
# Get the two keys from `npx supabase status` after `npm run db:start`.
# These local keys are fixed across restarts — set them once.
SUPABASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:54321
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=replace-with-local-anon-key
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=replace-with-local-service-role-key

# ── Hosted Supabase project (cloud / production deploy target) ────────────────
# From Dashboard → Project Settings → API. Keep these COMMENTED OUT so the
# seed/tests keep targeting local — uncomment-and-swap (or pass inline) only
# for a deliberate one-off against the cloud project.
# NEVER run `npm run db:reset` or `npm test` against the cloud project.
# The service_role/secret key must never ship in a client app or be committed.
# SUPABASE_URL=https://<your-project-ref>.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=<anon-or-publishable-key>
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=<service_role-or-secret-key>
